From: omarchy-extras <jabbslad@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Fri, 17 Apr 2026 21:40:00 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] media: pci: ipu-bridge: add Samsung SC200PC (SSLC2000)

The Samsung Galaxy Book6 Pro (NP940XJG-KGDUK, Panther Lake) exposes its
internal front camera as ACPI HID "SSLC2000". The sensor is a SmartSens /
Samsung-branded SC200PC at I2C3/0x36.

`intel-ipu7` falls back to `ipu_bridge_init(..., ipu_bridge_parse_ssdb)` when
the IPU PCI device has no firmware-node graph, but `ipu-bridge` only creates
software-node endpoints for sensors listed in `ipu_supported_sensors[]`.

Without an SSLC2000 entry:

  - a sensor driver can still bind at the I2C level via ACPI
  - the sensor's ACPI device has a primary fwnode only, no secondary
    software-node graph
  - `intel-ipu7` logs "no subdev found in graph" and never registers a
    media entity for the sensor

Add SSLC2000 to the supported-sensors table. Follow the INTC10C5 precedent
and leave `nr_link_freqs = 0`: the link-frequencies fwnode property is then
omitted (see `ipu_bridge_create_fwnode_properties`, cfg->nr_link_freqs > 0
guard), which is correct while the link-frequency value for this sensor is
still unconfirmed. The companion sensor driver may expose link_freq via a
V4L2 control once finalized.

Base: Linux v6.19.10 (byte-identical to archlinux/linux v6.19.10-arch1).

Signed-off-by: omarchy-extras <jabbslad@users.noreply.github.com>
---
 drivers/media/pci/intel/ipu-bridge.c | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/media/pci/intel/ipu-bridge.c b/drivers/media/pci/intel/ipu-bridge.c
--- a/drivers/media/pci/intel/ipu-bridge.c
+++ b/drivers/media/pci/intel/ipu-bridge.c
@@ -95,6 +95,8 @@ static const struct ipu_sensor_config ipu_supported_sensors[] = {
 	IPU_SENSOR_CONFIG("OVTI8856", 3, 180000000, 360000000, 720000000),
 	/* Sony IMX471 */
 	IPU_SENSOR_CONFIG("SONY471A", 1, 200000000),
+	/* Samsung/SmartSens SC200PC */
+	IPU_SENSOR_CONFIG("SSLC2000", 0),
 	/* Toshiba T4KA3 */
 	IPU_SENSOR_CONFIG("XMCC0003", 1, 321468000),
 };
